(You): Aside from graphviz, what good free graph-creating tools are out there? I'm talking about mathematical graphs (vertices and edges), not "chart graphs". Are there any graph-creating tools that guarentee a planar graph will be drawn in a planar fashion?

(Daniel): gnuplot

(You): gnuplot doesn't deal with graphs at all, does it? Not mathematical ones anyway?

(Daniel): gnuplot was specifically designed to do mathematical graphing.

(You): I'm pretty sure we're talking about different meanings of the word graph, but OK: how do I get gnuplot to display K4 (the complete graph on 4 vertices) planarly?

