(Tamvana): I think the Boost graph library can do planar embeddings of graphs. If that doesn't work for you, a little bit of poking around suggests you might have luck with JGraphEd, WilmaScope or VGJ.

(You): OK, I've installed the boost library. Does it give me any command-line tools or can I only write C++ programs with it?

(Tamvana): Only C++ programs, but there are examples online of how to do the kind of thing you want to do. (Just search for "Boost planarity")

